# Google Cloud Text-to-Speech Configuration
# Copy this to your .env file and update the path

# Path to Google Cloud service account key JSON file
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/your/service-account-key.json

# Example for Windows:
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=C:\Users\YourName\pixeltales-tts-key.json

# Example for Linux/Mac:
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/home/yourname/pixeltales-tts-key.json

# How to get the key:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Create a project or select existing
# 3. Enable "Cloud Text-to-Speech API"
# 4. Go to IAM & Admin â†’ Service Accounts
# 5. Create service account with "Cloud Text-to-Speech User" role
# 6. Create and download JSON key
# 7. Update the path above
